summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2010 JAGUAR XF. THE CONTACTED OBSERVED FUEL LEAKING FROM THE FUEL TANK OF THE REAR PASSENGER SIDE WHILE FUELING THE VEHICLE. IN ADDITION, THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE CHECK ENGINE INDICATOR AND FILLER CAP WARNING SENSOR WERE ILLUMINATED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO THE LOCAL DEALER (LAND ROVER OF HOFFMAN LOCATED ON 1051 W HIGGINS RD, HOFFMAN ESTATES, IL, 60169) AND WAS INFORMED THAT THE VEHICLE WAS NOT INCLUDED IN A RECALL FOR THE FUEL. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT DIAGNOSED DUE TO THE DIAGNOSTIC FEES. THE VIN WAS NOT INCLUDED IN NHTSA CAMPAIGN NUMBER: 12V521000 (FUEL SYSTEM). THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS APPROXIMATELY 105,000.
